  <string name="label_external_ime_link_aidl">Allow external IME linking (AIDL)</string>
  <string name="external_aidl_guide_title">How to Use the Linking Feature</string>
  <string name="external_aidl_guide_message">This feature enables voice recognition from Fcitx (Little Penguin) input method. Usage:\n\n1. Download the modified Fcitx: https://github.com/BryceWG/fcitx5-android-lexi-keyboard/releases (uninstall the original Fcitx first and backup your data)\n\n2. Open Fcitx Settings - Virtual Keyboard - Long-press Space Bar Behavior - Voice Input (AIDL)\n\n3. Update LexiSharp to 3.6.2 or later, enable Settings - Input Settings - Allow external IME linking (AIDL), no need to enable floating ball or accessibility service\n\n4. In Fcitx keyboard panel, long-press the space bar to activate voice input.</string>
